Hello, my team is struggling with figuring out how to set up auto group with pathplanner. We are trying to make it so our launcher launches a note and then moves away. We created a “shoot” command that we added as an event marker in the pathplanner software. I’m unsure if I’m implementing the commands correctly. What’s happening is that the auto is driving, but not running the shoot command.

Our code can be found on our github here: GitHub - vickitine404/2024MainTestChassis-main

The autos are being called in robotContainer, and pathplanner is set up in the pathplanner files.

Any help would be greatly appreciated.

Your single PathPlanner auto contains only a path and no event markers.

In RobotContainer, it looks like you’re trying to call getAutoPath before you call registerCommand, which won’t work.

You should consider using buildAutoChooser.

Yes. Your shoot command has isFinished return false so will never end. There are a number of ways to fix this, but the simplest is probably to use the withTimeout wrapper when you call registerCommand. That way you can register multiple variants, e.g.:

NamedCommands.registerCommand("shoot_2s", 
    new shoot(s_Indexer, s_Launcher).withTimeout(2));
